article.headline: Buffalo 68, N. Illinois 46
article.story: AMHERST, N.Y. -- Rodney Pierce led Buffalo with 15 points in a 68-46 win over Northern Illinois in Mid-American Conference basketball Saturday. Andy Robinson scored 12 points and grabbed seven rebounds. Vadim Fedotov added another 10 points for Buffalo. Darion Anderson led Northern Illinois (6-15, 2-7) with a game-high 16 points. Mike DiNunno also scored 10 for the Huskies. Buffalo (16-5, 8-1) managed to keep an opponent under 50 points for the second time in one week. Northern Illinois went just 18-of-48 from the field while committing 20 turnovers which the Bulls converted into 26 points. Buffalo also dominated the boards, out-rebounding Northern Illinois 44-28. Eleven different Bulls found their way onto the score sheet as Buffalo?s reserves contributed 37 points.
